= Experimental Chapter 1

Each experimental chapter should be a self-contained piece of work that addresses a specific research question or hypothesis. The structure below is a suggestion; adapt it to suit your research. A PhD thesis may contain multiple studies within a single chapter, or dedicate one chapter per study — discuss the best approach with your supervisor.

== Introduction

Introduce the research question or hypothesis addressed in this chapter, and explain how it relates to the overall thesis aims and the gaps identified in the literature review.

== Related Work

If this chapter draws on literature not covered in the main literature review (e.g., specific to this study's methodology or domain), include a focused related work section here. This keeps each chapter self-contained while avoiding unnecessary repetition of the main review.

== Methodology

Describe the research methodology and experimental design used in this chapter.

=== Research Questions and Hypotheses

State the specific research questions and/or hypotheses for this study.

=== Measures and Instruments

Describe the instruments, questionnaires, or metrics used to collect data.

=== Participants and Procedure

Detail participant recruitment (including sample size justification), demographics, and the step-by-step experimental procedure.

=== Data Analysis

Describe the analytical methods used (statistical tests, qualitative coding, etc.) and justify their selection.

== Implementation

If this chapter involves a software artefact, system, or tool, detail its design and implementation here. Include architecture overviews, key design decisions, and any relevant technical details. For studies using existing systems, describe the experimental setup and configuration.

== Results

Present the results of the study with supporting figures, tables, and statistical analyses. Organise by research question or hypothesis where appropriate.

== Summary of Findings

Briefly summarise the key findings of this study before moving to discussion. This is particularly helpful in chapters containing multiple sub-studies.

== Discussion

Discuss the implications of the results, how they relate to the literature, and what they mean for the overall thesis. Consider how these findings address (or fail to address) the research questions posed in this chapter.

== Limitations

Acknowledge the limitations specific to this study. Being transparent about limitations strengthens the academic rigour of the work and helps frame the contributions appropriately.

== Conclusion

Briefly conclude this chapter, summarising its contribution and providing a transition to the next chapter.
